{"title_page": "2007\u201308 Aberdeen F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n| club          = [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]\n| season        = 2007\u201308\n| manager       = [[Jimmy Calderwood]]\n| chairman      = [[Stewart Milne]]\n| stdtitle      = Stadium\n| stadium       = [[Pittodrie Stadium]]\n| league        = [[2007\u201308 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]]\n| league result = 4th\n| cup1          = [[2007\u201308 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]\n| cup1 result   = Semi-finals\n| cup2          = [[2007\u201308 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]]\n| cup2 result   = Semi-finals\n| league topscorer   = <br />[[Lee Miller (footballer)|Lee Miller]] (13)\n| season topscorer   = <br />[[Lee Miller (footballer)|Lee Miller]] (13)\n| highest attendance = 20,446 (v [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]], 20 December 2007)\n| lowest attendance  = 7,270 (v [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness CT]], 31 October 2007)\n| average attendance = 12,888\n| prevseason = [[2006\u201307 Aberdeen F.C. season|2006\u201307]]\n| nextseason = [[2008\u201309 Aberdeen F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n}}\n'''[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]''' competed in the [[2007\u201308 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]], [[2007\u201308 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]], [[2007\u201308 Scottish League Cup|Scottish League Cup]] and [[2007\u201308 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] in '''season 2007\u201308'''. It was the club's first season in European competition since 2002\u201303.\n\nQualification for the group stages of the UEFA Cup was secured with an [[Away goals rule|away-goals]] qualifying victory over [[FC Dnipro Dnipropetrovsk]]. Aberdeen were drawn in Group B along with [[Panathinaikos FC|Panathinaikos]], [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]], [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] and [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]]. Aberdeen qualified for the round of 32 following a 4\u20130 victory over F.C. Copenhagen. They were drawn against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and lost 7\u20133 on aggregate, but did manage a 2\u20132 home draw with the German club.\n\n==Transfers and other changes==\n{| class=\"infobox\" style=\"font-size:90%; padding:1px\" width=30%\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:105%\" |Summer Transfers\n|-bgcolor=\"#EFEFEF\"\n! Player in !! From !! Fee\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Lee Mair]] || [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] || [[Bosman ruling|Bosman]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jonathan Kurrant]] || [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] || Free <ref>[http://www.totallyjewish.com/sport/?content_id=6278 Kurrant's A Don] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927221809/http://www.totallyjewish.com/sport/?content_id=6278 |date=27 September 2007 }}, TotallyJemish.com, 16 May 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jackie McNamara]] || [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolves]] || Free <ref>\n[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6667595.stm Wolves' McNamara joins Aberdeen], BBC Sport, 18 May 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|NED}} [[Jeffrey de Visscher]] || [[De Graafschap]] || Free <ref>\n[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6684531.stm Dons swoop to sign Dutch winger], BBC Sport, 30 May 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Derek Young]] || [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]] || Free <ref>\n[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6913468.stm Calderwood welcomes Young return], BBC Sport, 25 July 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jonathan Smith (footballer born 1988)|Jonathan Smith]] || [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan]] || Free <ref name=\"English Strikers\">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6969302.stm Dons bring in two young strikers], BBC Sport, 31 August 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Sone Aluko]] || [[Birmingham F.C.|Birmingham]] || Loan <ref name=\"English Strikers\"/>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EFEFEF\"\n! Player out !! To !! Fee\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jamie Winter]] || [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] || Free <ref>\n[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/chesterfield/6909103.stm Chesterfield set to sign Winter], BBC Sport, 20 July 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[David Donald (footballer)|David Donald]] || [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]] || Free\n|-\n| {{flagicon|IRE}} [[Gary Dempsey (Irish footballer)|Gary Dempsey]] || [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] || Free <ref>[http://www.afc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/News/clubNewsDetail/0,,10284~1002114,00.html Dempsey to Depart Dons]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, Aberdeen FC, 26 March 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|NED}} [[Dyron Daal]] || [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] || Free <ref>\n[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/st_johnstone/6731057.stm St Johnstone seal Daal transfer], BBC Sport, 7 June 2007</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Russell Anderson]] || [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] || \u00a31 Million\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Craig Brewster]] || [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness CT]] || Free\n|}\n\n===Summer transfers===\n[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] had already announced that the contracts of [[Jamie Winter]] and [[David Donald (footballer)|David Donald]] were not to be renewed. [[Gary Dempsey (Irish footballer)|Gary Dempsey]] rejected a new two-year deal to sign for [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]], and [[Dyron Daal]] left to join [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]].\n\n[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] had secured the signatures of defenders [[Lee Mair]] from [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]], and youngster [[Jonathan Kurrant]], who would join after he had finished his A-Levels. Both agreed pre-contracts. [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolves]] experienced defender [[Jackie McNamara]] and [[De Graafschap]] winger [[Jeffrey de Visscher]] both signed on [[Free transfer (football)|free transfers]]. Former player Derek Young returned to the club on a free transfer after spells at Dunfermline and Partick Thistle. [[Sone Aluko]] was signed on a free loan deal from [[Birmingham F.C.|Birmingham]].\n\n'''Jamie Langfield'''<br />\nOn 8 June 2007 it had been reported that [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen's]] first-choice goalkeeper [[Jamie Langfield]] had been demoted after falling out with manager [[Jimmy Calderwood]]. The fall-out was believed to have been related to [[Jimmy Calderwood|Calderwood's]] decision to reject a \u00a370,000 offer from [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]. The club later confirmed that they had made [[Jamie Langfield|Langfield]] available for transfer, with an asking price of \u00a3100,000.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6733421.stm Keeper pays for stag night antics], BBC Sport, 8 June 2007</ref>\nLangfield was recalled to the starting line-up for the UEFA Cup game against Dnipro at Pittodrie on 20 September.\nThe day after Aberdeen's UEFA cup victory over FC Copenhagen on 20 December 2007, Langfield signed a new three-year contract with Aberdeen.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/7156144.stm Langfield nets new Aberdeen deal ], BBC Sport, 21 December 2007</ref>\n\n'''Russell Anderson'''<br />\nOn 27 June 2007 club captain [[Russell Anderson]] moved to [[Premier League|Premiership]] side [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]. He signed a 3-year contract with the club, but also donated his signing-on fee to the youth development scheme at [[Pittodrie Stadium|Pittodrie]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/6244320.stm Anderson seals Sunderland switch], BBC Sport, 27 June 2007</ref>\n\n===Winter transfers===\n{| class=\"infobox\" style=\"font-size:90%; padding:1px\" width=30%\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:105%\" | Winter Transfers\n|-bgcolor=\"#EFEFEF\"\n! Player in !! From !! Fee\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Stuart Duff]] || [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] || Free <ref name=\"English Strikers\"/>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Josh Walker (English footballer)|Josh Walker]] || [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] || Loan <ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/7215897.stm Boro midfielder in Dons loan move], BBC Sport, 29 January 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|NED}} [[Dave Bus]] || [[De Graafschap]] || Free <ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/7207975.stm Defender Bus makes Aberdeen stop] BBC Sport, 24 January 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|IRE}} [[Alan Maybury]] || [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] || Free <ref name=\"Foxes' Maybury joins Dons on loan\">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/heart_of_midlothian/7200659.stm Foxes' Maybury joins Dons on loan] BBC Sport, 31 January 2008.</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EFEFEF\"\n! Player out !! To !! Fee\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Chris Clark (footballer, born 1980)|Chris Clark]] || [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] || \u00a3200,000 <ref name=\"Plymouth snap up Aberdeen's Clark\">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/7192692.stm Plymouth snap up Aberdeen's Clark], BBC Sport, 16 January 2008</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Michael Hart (footballer)|Michael Hart]] || [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] || Undisclosed <ref name=\"Plymouth snap up Aberdeen's Clark\"/>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Michael Paton]] || [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]] || Loan\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Stuart Smith || [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]] || Loan <ref name=\"Foxes' Maybury joins Dons on loan\"/>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Neil McVitie]] || [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]] || Loan <ref name=\"Foxes' Maybury joins Dons on loan\"/>\n|}\n\n[[Chris Clark (footballer, born 1980)|Chris Clark]] was the first player to leave Aberdeen in the January window after signing a three-and-a-half-year deal with [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]. The clubs agreed a fee of \u00a3200,000 for the midfielder who had played at Aberdeen for seven years. Michael Paton extended his loan deal with [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]] until the end of the season. Striker Stuart Smith and defender Neil McVitie both went on loan to [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]] until the end of the season.\n\n[[Stuart Duff]] was Aberdeen's first signing of the January transfer window. They signed the midfielder from [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] on a free transfer. [[Sone Aluko]] agreed to extend his loan from [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] until the end of the season.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/7188521.stm], BBC Sport, 14 January 2008.</ref> Defender Dave Bus was signed from [[De Graafschap]] until the end of the season. Aberdeen signed [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] midfielder and [[England national under-18 football team|England under-18]] captain [[Josh Walker (English footballer)|Josh Walker]] on a loan deal until the end of the season. The [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] international [[Alan Maybury]] was signed from [[Leicester City|Leicester]] on a loan deal until the end of the season.\n\n'''Michael Hart'''<br />\nAfter [[Michael Hart (footballer)|Michael Hart]] rejected a new deal with Aberdeen, a fee thought to be in the region of \u00a3200,000 was agreed between Aberdeen and [[Preston North End]] for his transfer.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/preston/7181210.stm Dons defender agrees Preston move],  BBC Sport, 14 January 2008</ref> However, Preston reduced their offer after carrying out medical tests on an injury due to keep him out for weeks.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/preston/7199979.stm Dons reject Preston's Hart offer],  BBC Sport, 26 January 2008</ref> Aberdeen refused to release the player unless Preston pay the agreed fee. He eventually moved to Preston for an undisclosed fee thought to be in the region of \u00a3100,000.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/preston/7199979.stm Dons' Hart completes Preston move],  BBC Sport, 30 January 2008</ref>\n\n===Summer clearout===\nIt was announced on 15 April that seven contracted players would be leaving at the end of the season,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aberdeen/7349238.stm Nicholson joins six leaving Dons ],  BBC Sport, 15 April 2008</ref> [[Barry Nicholson]] decided to leave, rejecting a new deal. The other six players were all not offered new deals, these were; Goalkeepers [[Derek Soutar]] (who had replaced Jamie Langfield for a large part of the season) and [[Greg Kelly (footballer)|Greg Kelly]], defenders [[Richie Byrne]] and [[Dave Bus]] and strikers [[Jonathan Smith (footballer born 1988)|Jonathan Smith]] and [[Steve Lovell]]. Loan signings [[Sone Aluko]] and [[Josh Walker (English footballer)|Josh Walker]] returned to their clubs at the end of their loan periods.\n\nOn 21 April defender [[Jackie McNamara]] was released from his contract by the club.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Pre-season friendlies===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Opponent\n!H/A\n!Score<ref name=\"Aberdeen score\">Aberdeen's score is shown first.</ref>\n!Aberdeen Scorers<ref name=\"scorers\">The number(s) in brackets shows the minute the goal(s) was/were scored.</ref>\n|-bgcolor=#ddffdd\n|12 July||[[Cove Rangers F.C.|Cove Rangers]]||align=center|[[Allan Park, Aberdeen|A]]||align=center|5\u20131||Maguire (19), Miller (43, 65), De Visscher (52), Lovell (90)\n|-bgcolor=#ddffdd\n|15 July||[[Buckie Thistle F.C.|Buckie Thistle]]||align=center|[[Victoria Park, Buckie|A]]||align=center|3\u20130||Brewster (31, 52), Mackie (88)\n|-bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n|18 July||{{flagicon|EGY}} [[El Mokawloon SC|Al Mokawloon]]||align=center|[[Alexandria Stadium|A]]||align=center|0\u20132||\n|-bgcolor=#ddffdd\n|21 July||{{flagicon|EGY}} [[Al Aluminium SC|Al Aluminium]]||align=center|[[Alexandria Stadium|A]]||align=center|2\u20130||Brewster (47), Foster (66)\n|-bgcolor=#ddffdd\n|23 July||{{flagicon|EGY}} [[Al Ittihad Alexandria Club|Al Ittihad]]||align=center|[[Alexandria Stadium|A]]||align=center|2\u20131||de Vissc