egory:Grade I listed parks and gardens in London]]\n[[Category:Charles Barry buildings]]\n", "name_user": "SG12341234", "label": "safe", "comment": "I cleared some aspects of this marvelous place, I also corrected some grammar issues regarding the square. I really think that all of the facts are up to date. I think no more editions should be made. Though I might be wrong. I doubled checked and everything was great.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trafalgar_Square"}
{"title_page": "Parc Jae-jung", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|South Korean Singer}}\n{{for|the actor|Park Jae-jung}}\n{{Korean name|Parc}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Parc Jae-jung \n| background      = solo_singer\n| image           = 171027 \ubc15\uc7ac\uc815.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = Parc in 2017\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1995|12|25}}\n| birth_place     = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| alias           = Parc Jaejung \n| genre           = [[Pop ballad]]\n| occupation      = Singer\n| instrument      = Guitar\n| years_active    = 2013\u2013present\n| label           = {{ubl|[[Stone Music Entertainment|CJ E&M]]|[[Mystic Entertainment]]}}\n| associated_acts = \n| website         = {{Official website|mystic89.net/artist/jaejung-parc}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name\n| child   = yes\n| hangul  = \ubc15\uc7ac\uc815\n| rr      = Bak Jae-jeong\n| mr      = Pak Chaech\u014fng\n}}\n}}\n'''Parc Jae-jung''' (born December 25, 1995)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2013/09/28/2013092800500.html|title='\uc288\ud37c\uc2a4\ud0c0K5' TOP9 \ud504\ub85c\ud544 \uacf5\uac1c..\uc608\uc0c1 \ub4f1\uc218\ub294?|last=Lee|first=Hye-lynn|date=September 28, 2013|work=The Chosun Ilbo|access-date=July 20, 2018|language=ko}}</ref> is a South Korean singer. He is well known as the winner of the South Korean singing competition ''[[Superstar K 5]]'' in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/51478/ssks-winner-park-jae-jung-feels-confident-about-his-upcoming-performance|title=Park Jae-jung Says His Performance at 2013 MAMA will be Mistake-Free|last=Na-rae|first=Lee|date=November 22, 2013|website=Mnet|publisher=CJ E&M|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140218051545/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/51478/ssks-winner-park-jae-jung-feels-confident-about-his-upcoming-performance|archive-date=February 18, 2014|url-status=|accessdate=May 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nParc was born in [[Seoul]], South Korea on December 25, 1995.<ref name=\":0\" /> He developed an interest in music at a young age and learned to play the violin, clarinet, and traditional Korean percussion instruments when he was in elementary school. In 2011, he moved with his family to Florida, where his parents worked as farmers''.''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2017/06/28/0200000000AKR20170628183400005.HTML|title=\ubc15\uc7ac\uc815 '\ubc1c\ub77c\ub4dc\uacc4\uc758 \uc801\uc790? \uc724\uc885\uc2e0\uc758 \uc81c\uc790\uc77c \ubfd0\uc774\uc8e0'|last=Lee|first=Eun-jeong|date=June 28, 2017|work=Yonhap News|access-date=July 20, 2018|language=ko-KR}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn July 2013, Parc participated in the fifth season of singing competition series ''[[Superstar K5]]''. On November 15, 2013 Parc was announced as the winner of the competition and having opportunity to signing with [[Stone Music Entertainment|CJ E&M]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.star.mt.co.kr/view.html?no=2013111522470079600&outlink=1&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.naver.com#imadnews |title='\u011b\u0160\u02c6\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u011b\u017a\u20ac5' \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \u011b\u013e\u0153\u011b\u2014\u00b0\u011b\u2020\u0152 \u011b\u0161\u00b0\u011b\u0160\u0161 \"\u011b\"\u0105\u011b\u017e\u013d\u00ed\u2022\u00b4 \u00eb?\u0152\u011b\u2022\"\u011b\u02dc\u0179\u0119\u02db\u0192\"(\u011b\u02d8\u2026\u00ed\u2022\u0160) - \u011b\u0160\u00a4\u00ed\u0192\u20ac\u00eb\u2030\u00b4\u011b\u0160\u00a4 |website=M.star.mt.co.kr |date=2013-11-16 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0002398324 |title='\u011b\u0160\u02c6\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u011b\u017a\u20ac5 \u011b\u0161\u00b0\u011b\u0160\u0161' \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \"MAMA \u00eb?\u00b0\u00eb\u02c7\" \u00eb\u0179\u00b4\u00eb\u0152\u20ac, \u011b\u02dc\u00a4\u00eb\u0160\u02dc \u0119\u00b0\u2122\u011b?\u20ac \u011b\u2039\u00a4\u011b\u02c6\u02dc \u011b\u2014\u2020\u00eb?\"\u00eb\u0104?\u00e2\u20ac\u015a\" |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2013-11-16 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref> On November 20, Parc released his pre-debut single \"Stalker\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000404873 |title=\u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u011b\u0160\u02c6\u00ed?\u017a\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u00ed\u0192\u20acK5\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022 \u0119\u0142\u013e\u011b\u2022\u02dd\u00e2\u20ac\u015a\u00e2\u20ac\u0153\u00eb?\u00b0\u00eb\u02c7\"\u0119\u0142\u0104 1\u011b\u0153\"\u00ed\u2022\u02dc\u00eb\u0160\u00b4 \u011b\u2014\u0179\u011b\"\u0105\u00ed\u0152\u0179\u011b\u2014? \u00ed\u0160\u0161\u00eb\u0142\" \u00eb\u0179\u00b4\u00eb\u0152\u20ac\u00e2\u20ac? |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2013-11-20 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref> On November 22, Parc made his official debut stage on the annual award event [[Mnet Asian Music Award]] at Hongkong's Asia World Expo Arena.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000281574 |title=\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022 \"MAMA \u00eb\u0179\u00b4\u00eb\u0152\u20ac, \u011b\u2039\u00a4\u011b\u02c6\u02dc\u00ed\u2022\u02dc\u011b\u00a7\u20ac \u011b\u2022\u0160\u011b?\" \u0119\u02db\u0192\" |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2013-11-22 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0002427549 |title='2013 MAMA' \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022\u00c2\u02c7\u011b\u0141\u017a\u011b&#x;\u02c6\u011b&#x;\u02c6 \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u011b\u0160\u02c6\u00ed?\u017a\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u00ed\u0192\u20ac\u0119\u00b0\u20ac \u00eb\u00a7\u0152\u00eb'\u0179\u00eb\u2039\u00a4\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date= |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn July 17, 2014 Parc released his first EP, ''Step 1'', where contain of five track including the lead single \"Ice Ice Baby\" featuring [[Beenzino]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000360823 |title='\u011b\u0160\u02c6\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u011b\u017a\u20ac5' \u011b\u0161\u00b0\u011b\u0160\u0161\u011b\u017e? \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, 17\u011b?\u017a \u00eb?\u00b0\u00eb\u02c7\"\u0119\u0142\u0104 '\u011b\u2013\u017a\u011b?\u0152\u00eb\u2022\u0104' \u00eb\u00b0\u0153\u00ed'\u0153\u00e2\u20ac\u015a'\u00ed\u0152\u0152\u0119\u02db\u0160 \u00eb\u0142\u20ac\u011b\u2039 ' |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2014-07-17 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000235782 |title=\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u011b\u2013\u017a\u011b?\u0152\u00eb\u2022\u0104\u00e2\u20ac\u2122\u011b\u0153\u017a\u00eb\u0104\u0153 \u011b\u2014\u0179\u00eb\u015a\" \u011b'\u0179\u00eb\u0192\u013d\u00e2\u20ac\u015a\u00eb\u0161\u02c6\u011b\u00a7\u20ac\u00eb\u2026\u00b8\u011b\u2122\u20ac\u011b?\u02dc \u011b\u0104\u00b0\u00ed\u2022\u0160\u00eb?\" \u00eb\u02c6\u02c6\u0119\u00b8\u00b8 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2014-07-17 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, Parc joined Mystic Entertainment after his contract with CJ E&M ended.<ref>{{cite web|author=OSEN |url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110195842#imadnews |title='\uc288\uc2a4\ucf005' \uc6b0\uc2b9\uc790 \ubc15\uc7ac\uc815, \ubbf8\uc2a4\ud2f1 \uc804\uc18d\uacc4\uc57d..\uc724\uc885\uc2e0 \ud488\uc73c\ub85c - OSEN |website=Mosen.mt.co.kr |date=2015-07-08 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn May 19, 2016 Parc released collaboration single \"Two Men\" with [[Kyuhyun]]. They also made performance of \"Two Men\" in the variety show ''[[Radio Star (TV series)|Radio Star]]'' on May 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=081&aid=0002719881 |title=\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u00eb'? \u00eb'\u00a8\u011b\u017e?\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 \u011b\u0160\u02c6\u00ed?\u017a\u011b\u0141\u017a\u00eb\u2039\u02c6\u011b\u2013\u00b4 \u0119\u02c7\u0153\u00ed\u02dc\"\u0119\u0142\u017a \u00eb\u2039\u0179\u011b\u02dd\u00a4 \u00eb\"\u20ac\u011b\u2014\u0141 \u00e2\u20ac\u0153\u00eb\u00a7\u017d\u011b?\u20ac \u0119\u00b4\u20ac\u011b\u2039\u0179 \u0119\u00b0?\u011b'\u0179\u00ed\u2022\u02dc\u00eb\u2039\u00a4\u00e2\u20ac? |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2016-05-19 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002815019 |title=[\u00ed\u0152?\u011b\u2014\u2026\u00eb\u017d\u00a4\u011b\u00a7 &#93;\u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u00eb'? \u00eb'\u00a8\u011b\u017e?\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022x\u0119\u02c7\u0153\u00ed\u02dc\"\u011b?\u00b4 \u011b\" \u00eb\u0142\u00b4\u011b?\u00b4\u00eb\u0160\" \u00eb\u015e\u2026\u00ed'\u02c6 \u00eb\u00b0\u0153\u00eb?\u017a\u00eb\"\u0153 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2016-05-19 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn May 19, 2017 Parc released single \"Passport\", as a part of [[Yoon Jong-shin|Yoon Jongshin]]'s music project ''Monthly Yong Jongshin 2017 May''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=266012#_enliple |title=\ubc15\uac00\uc601 \uae30\uc790 - \uc724\uc885\uc2e0-\ubc15\uc7ac\uc815, '\uc5ec\uad8c' \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026'\uc2e0\uad6c \ubc1c\ub77c\ub354\uc758 \ub9cc\ub0a8' - \ud1b1\uc2a4\ud0c0\ub274\uc2a4 |website=Topstarnews.net |date= |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\nIn the same month, Parc was cast in the first season of the music variety show ''Snowball Project''. He team-up with Mark Lee of [[NCT (band)|NCT]] released \"Lemonade Love\" on July 21, which was produced by [[Henry Lau]] and [[Yoon Jong-shin|Yoon Jongshin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=014&aid=0003847621 |title=\u00e2\u20ac\u0153\u00eb\u02c6\u02c6\u00eb?\u0160\u011b?\u00b4 \u011b\u015b\u0153\u0119\u02db\u0160\u00e2\u20ac?...\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022X\u00eb\u00a7\u02c6\u00ed \u0179, \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u00eb \u02c6\u00eb\u015e\u00a8\u00eb\"\u00a4\u011b?\u00b4\u00eb\"\u0153 \u00eb&#x;\u0179\u00eb\u00b8\u0152\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 \u011b\u02dc\u00a4\u00eb\u0160\u02dc(21\u011b?\u017a) \u00eb\u00b0\u0153\u00ed'\u0153 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2017-07-21 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/05/23/sm-mystic-entertainment-team-new-music-variety-show/|title=Parc Jae Jung And NCT's Mark Are The First Team-Up For SM And Mystic Entertainment's New Variety Show {{!}} Soompi|website=www.soompi.com|access-date=October 7, 2017}}</ref> In August 2017, Parc was cast in the 2017 MBC pilot variety show ''[[It's Dangerous Beyond The Blankets]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pauly|first=C|title=\"It's Dangerous Beyond The Blankets\" Cast Are The Most Relatable Introverts|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/08/27/dangerous-beyond-blanket-cast-relatable-introverts/|date=August 27, 2017|accessdate=September 17, 2017}}</ref> On June 29, Parc released his single \"Focus\", which was written by [[Yoon Jong-shin|Yoon Jongshin]] and Jung Suk-won of 015B.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003567196 |title=\"\u011b\u0153\u00a4\u011b\u02d8\u2026\u011b' X\u011b \u2022\u011b\"?\u011b'? \u00ed\u2022\u0160\u011b\u017e'\u00ed'\u02c6\"..\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, '\u011b'\u0153\u00eb \u013d' \u011b\u02dc\u00a4\u00eb\u0160\u02dc 6\u011b'\u0153 \u0119\u0142\u013e\u0119\u00b0\u0153 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2017-06-29 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.breaknews.com/a.html?uid=517365&section=sc4#cb |title=[\ud55c\uad6d\uc5b8\ub860\uc758 \uc138\ub300\uad50\uccb4 \u25c6\ube0c\ub808\uc774\ud06c\ub274\uc2a4\u25c6&#93; \ucc28\uc138\ub300 \ubc1c\ub77c\ub354 \ubc15\uc7ac\uc815, \uccab \uc194\ub85c\uace1 '\uc2dc\ub825' 29\uc77c \uc624\ud6c4 6\uc2dc \uacf5\uac1c..'\uad00\uc2ec\u2191' |website=M.breaknews.com |date=2017-06-29 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref> On October 13, Parc released another single \"The Villain\", which also written by [[Yoon Jong-shin|Yoon Jongshin]] and Jung Suk-won of 015B. The single is the trilogy of the farewell ballad following \"Two Men\" and \"Focus\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002964664 |title=\"\u00eb\u02dc? \u00ed\u2022\u0153 \u00eb\u02db\u02c6 \u011b\"\u0105\u011b\u017e\u013d\"..\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \u011b?\u00b4\u00eb\u0142\" \u00eb\u00b0\u0153\u00eb?\u017a\u00eb\"\u0153 '\u011b\u2022\u2026\u011b\u2014' \u011b\u02dc\u00a4\u00eb\u0160\u02dc(13\u011b?\u017a) \u0119\u0142\u013e\u0119\u00b0\u0153 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2017-10-13 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>[https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002717583 ]{{dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref>\nOn December 18, Parc held his first solo concert '''Mood In December''' at Seoul's Hyundai Card Understage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003682694 |title=\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022, \u011b\u02db\u0164 \u00eb\u2039\u00a8\u00eb?\u2026\u011b\u02dd\u02dc\u011b\"\u0153\u00ed\u0160\u00b8 \u011b\"\u0105\u00eb\u0141\u0152..\u00e2\u20ac\u0153\u00eb?\" \u011b\"\u0105\u011b\u017e\u013d\u00ed\u2022\u0153 \u00eb\u015e\u00a8\u011b\u0160\u013e \u00eb\u0142\u00b4\u011b\u2014\u0179\u011b\u00a4\" \u0119\u02db\u0192\u00e2\u20ac? |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date=2017-12-18 |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nOn June 8, 2018 Parc released single \"Bad Dreams\", as a part of [[Mystic Entertainment]]'s music project ''LISTEN''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=396&aid=0000481927 |title=\u00eb\u017b\u00b8\u011b\u0160\u00a4\u00ed\u2039\u0105 LISTEN, 26\u00eb\u02db\u02c6\u011b\u00a7\u00b8 \u0119\u0142\u0104\u011b?\u20ac \u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022\u011b?\u02dc \u00e2\u20ac\u02dc\u00eb\u2039\u02c6\u0119\u00b0\u20ac \u011b\u0141\u02dd\u00eb\u0160\" \u0119\u017c\u02c6\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date= |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref> His next single \"Words\" was released on August 4, which is his first self-composed song since debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201808041013322410&r=1&http_referer=https%3A%2F%2Fm.search.naver.com%2Fsearch.naver%3Fquery%3D%25EB%25B0%2595%25EC%259E%25AC%25EC%25A0%2595%2B%25EA%25B0%2580%25EC%2582%25AC%26sm%3Dmtb_hty.top%26where%3Dm_news%26oquery%3D%25EB%25B0%2595%25EC%259E%25AC%25EC%25A0%2595%2B%25EB%258B%2588%25EA%25B0%2580%2B%25EC%25A3%25BD%25EB%258A%2594%2B%25EA%25BF%2588%26tqi%3DT3pV6dpySAhssbmKj%252F4sssssttK-507486 |title=\ubc15\uc7ac\uc815, \ub370\ubdd4 4\ub144\ub9cc \uccab \uc790\uc791\uace1 '\uac00\uc0ac' \uc624\ub298(4\uc77c) \uacf5\uac1c - \ub274\uc2a4\uc5d4 |website=M.newsen.com |date= |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003836858 |title=[\u00ed\u2021\u00b4\u0119\u02c7\u017a\u0119\u00b8\u00b8 \u011b\u2039 \u0119\u0142\u0104&#93; \"\u0119\u02c7\u00b8\u00eb\u2026\u20ac\u0119\u00b0\u20ac \u00eb\"\u00a4\u011b\u2013\u00b4\u011b\u0141\u017a\u0119\u00b8\u00b8 \u00eb\u00b0\"\u00eb\u017e?\u00eb\u2039\u02c6\u00eb\u2039\u00a4\"\u00e2\u20ac\u015a\u00eb\u00b0\u2022\u011b\u017e\u0179\u011b \u2022\u011b?\u02dc \u011b\u02db\u0164\u00eb\u02db\u02c6\u011b\u00a7\u00b8 \u0119\u00b0?\u011b\"\u0105 '\u0119\u00b0\u20ac\u011b'\u0179' |website=M.entertain.naver.com |date= |accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Album details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5em;\"|Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Sales\n|-\n! <small>[[Gaon Album Chart|KOR]]</small><br /><ref name=\"gaon_album_chart\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T|title=Gao